body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Taylor's Car Dealership. My name is Edward Taylor. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Ashley. Could you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you. And may I have your email address as well?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Ashley. I appreciate your cooperation.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling disappointed with the recent billing issue.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'm sorry to hear that. Let me look into it for you. Thank you for bringing this to our attention.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time today, Ashley. We will work to resolve this issue promptly. Goodbye.
